Wits University Vice Chancellor Professor Zeblon Vilakazi says the institution has allocated R70 million to help students as part of its hardship fund. #eNCA​ Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Wits University Vice-Chancellor Professor Zeblon Vilakazi says the institution has allocated R70 million to help students as part of its hardship fund. Vilakazi says, this year, Wits added another R10 million as a once-off COVID-19 relief fund to deal with student financial issues. READ: Nzimande wants explanation on Mthokozisi Ntumba's death This R10 million can only be accessed by students badly affected by the COVID-19 pandemic. Vilakazi also says management and students have met on several occasions to discuss funding issues. Watch the video above for more on this story.